    <thetext>+++ This bug was initially created as a clone of Bug #207873 +++
Original Description:
The persistence-unit-default for schema in the orm.xml is being ignored by Dali.  It is not becoming the default for validation, UI, etc.  This is a regression from 1.0.

Update:
I am seeing this problem with the org.eclipse.jpt.core_1.1.0.v200712030000.jar.

I believe it was fixed for 1.0, but not sure if that fix was ever brought into
the 2.0 stream.

I get validation errors complaining about the wrong schema, though it is set in
the orm.xml.  If I explicitly add the /META-INF/orm.xml mapping file into the
persistence.xml then it finds it and validates properly.  Should I open a new
bug for this?</thetext>
